pullsbody: By adding a beforeunload listener in the pagemod contentscript, the workers are forced destroyed whenever going back and forth through the paging.  Why?  I am guessing that the browser does caching on pages that have no beforeunload handler - this means that our workers are never torn down and never reinitialized when a page is reshown using the history.  Voodoo.
pull_repo_desc: A Firefox plugin to support BrowserID login in the browser as well as the Sessions API
pull_commit_message: Voodoo.  By adding a beforeunload listener in the pagemod contentscript, the workers are forced destroyed whenever going back and forth through the paging.  Why?  I am guessing that the browser does caching on pages that have no iframes and have no beforeunload handler.
